race.comment: BOTANICAL BOY (5) resumes for his second campaign having shown good ability in three runs last time in. He was a narrow maiden winner on debut here over 1000m before tackling a couple of handy BM64's before the spell. He's open to plenty of improvement in his second campaign and looks well placed. DELICATE LADY (3) was a smart winner as favourite on heavy ground at Kyneton to add to her consistent record. She handles all ground and should get a good run on speed. SUGAR COAT (6) ran a disappointing 12th last start at Cranbourne over 1400m when beaten 4.5 lengths. Talented gelding with plenty of upside. Forgive the last run. He can contest. THUNDER AWARD (7) scored over 1100m at Kilmore two back then found a couple better last time out over 1112m there. Looks a strong place chance.
